<br>
As the man began to rush at Hippolyte, Marpe sent her sword into the side of his shoulder.  He quicky turned around and faced the guardian with a dirty grin.  &quot;Die BEAST&quot; he screamed rushing at her with his sword held high.<br>
<br>
Marpe growled and met his sword with her own stopping it's fall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#993300>(3/12/03 1:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=88>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Her Arrival ( Sorry for being late, lot! )</span><hr size=1> Hearing Hippolyte's cry, Dessame out of her place of hiding, drawing her sword. She rushed out with the others, and a Roman came her way. She grinned as the came toward her, and she began to fight.<br>
<br>
The clanks of metal echoed through the forest as blade met blade and Dess kept the grin on her face the whole time. When the blades met again, she snorted and knocked his sword right out of his hand. She twirled, slashing at his stomach and then knocked him down.<br>
<br>
She turned to the other Roman as he her way, and kicked him in the stomach, then grabbed him in a headlock. While he struggled, she snapped his neck quickly and let him all to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hmph.&quot;<br>
<br>
Was all she said as she pickd up her discarded sword, and ran toward the others to aid them. <p>÷ Odessa Sayler Loire ÷<br>
