They rolled over and over, trying to loosen their grips on their swords. The soldier slammed her face into the ground. Solari stood up and removed her mother's helmet, seeing blood on the inside and feeling it crawl down her face. <br>
<br>
The soldier stood there, not believeing what he saw. He knew this amazon. &quot;Solari...how good it is to see you again.&quot; he said cooly. &quot;It will truly be a honour this time to kill you outside of the arena.&quot;  And he began swinging his sword at her.<br>
<br>
 Solari just kept her stare on him. Her anger flowed fast thru her body, filling every muscle...but she kept her edge. She countered all his blows with her own, knocking him to the ground several times. This was her way of toying with him. She wanted his death to be slow and painful.... <br>
<br>
