 <br>
 &quot;Solari...have mercy.&quot; the Roman said as he stood before her, bloodied and bruised. <br>
<br>
 &quot;Mercy?&quot; She asked coldly. &quot;Like you showed me friends...my sisters?&quot; Solari moved closer to him, dagger in hand. &quot;Your time on this world has come to an end. I am going to serve as your exocutioner as you served to my friends.&quot; <br>
<br>
 The soldier glared at her and made on more gesture towards Solari with his dagger. She moved to one side, then stepped back in front of him, her dagger raised. <br>
&quot;See you in tartarus. Tiberius.&quot; She answered as she rammed her dagger thru his throat. <br>
<br>
 As he slowly sank to the ground, Tiberius shoved his dagger into Solari's side. She cried out in pain as she felt the cold steel pierce her flesh. She kept cold eyes on the soldier as she twisted the dagger inside his throat. Tiberius made a gurggling sound as he fell backwards, the last remaining breath, gone with the thud he made on the ground. Solari grabbed her side, wincing as she pulled the Roman dagger out. She looked around at her fellow sister's as they were taking out the remaining soldiers. She sank to her knees, too weak to continue standing, placing a weak hand back on her wound in her side, she collasped.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A> at: 3/13/03 3:53:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://m1.cool.ne.jp/915/k_piyo00.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#993300>(3/13/03 6:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.pureshakira.com/images/gallery/shakira/aep.sized.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A debt is settled to fallen friends</span><hr size=1> It was moments like this that Kalasin loved. Fighting an enemy, smelling death around herself… it was just like the days back in Chin, where she could have had anything that she pleased…<br>
She met two men head-on, slashing at them ferociously with her silver blade. Her movements were fast, faster than most people would have thought of the tall woman. Her eyes flashed in the heat of the battle, and she found herself letting go of all the bounds that she knew.<br>
The amazon woman flipped over the bigger man and landed deftly behind him. She grabbed him from behind and savagely ran her sword across his throat, letting him fall to the ground and she went for the other man.<br>
There was no conversation in this fight, no witty banter, she was all business.<br>
The two sparred for a moment before Kalasin sent a spinning kick into the side of his head. It didn’t knock him off his feet, merely dazed him for a moment, but a moment was all she needed. She ran him through that moment, and then, seeing Solari collapse, she rushed over to her.<br>
<br>
“My Queen? My Queen? Are you okay?”<br>
